    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">50, Albemarle Street, | W.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>July 28. 1881</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Your letter has taken quite by surprise, as we had no idea that you intended to publish your “Worm” volume at this period of the year &amp; we wish to remonstrate with you about doing so.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>The paper has to be made &amp; so have the Stereotypes for America &amp; this has to be done before we can print off any copies.</p>
<p>Again Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Appleton will require to have the plates sometime <hi rend="underline">before</hi> we publish, so that they may be able to print off their edition for a simultaneous publication, or nearly so, in both countries.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>This must delay the work here for some 5 or 6 weeks &amp; it will ruin the success of the book to publish then.</p>
<p>Can you not then agree to defer the publication until October, when we shall be able to secure a good start, which will gratify both the author &amp; publisher &amp; please the booksellers.</p>
<p>We propose to print 1000 Copies &amp; ask Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Clowes to keep the type standing.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>With kind compliments | Yours faithfully | Rob<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. Cooke <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Cha<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. Darwin Esq</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD’s letter has not been found. <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref> had gone to press on 1 May 1881 and was published by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3463.xml">John Murray</ref> on 10 October 1881 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml">Freeman 1977</ref>). </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_135.xml">D. Appleton &amp; Co.</ref> were CD’s US publishers; they published from stereotypes of the British edition provided by Murray. Simultaneous publication would reduce Appleton’s losses on account of pirated editions.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_979.xml">William Clowes &amp; Sons</ref> were Murray’s printers.</note>
        </div>
    
